{"id":"Ghost__Post__60b08e9903ca89001c10894c","title":"Raspberry Pi - How to install Samba","slug":"raspberry-pi-how-to-install-samba","featured":false,"feature_image":"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/img.png","excerpt":"\bSamba is the standard windows interoperability suite of programs for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file and print services for all clients using the SMB/CIFS protocol, such as all versions of DOS and Windows, OS/2, Linux and many others.","custom_excerpt":"\bSamba is the standard windows interoperability suite of programs for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file and print services for all clients using the SMB/CIFS protocol, such as all versions of DOS and Windows, OS/2, Linux and many others.","visibility":"public","created_at_pretty":"28 May 2021","published_at_pretty":"29 May 2021","updated_at_pretty":"29 May 2021","created_at":"2021-05-28T15:32:57.000+09:00","published_at":"2021-05-29T10:06:00.000+09:00","updated_at":"2021-05-29T10:06:56.000+09:00","meta_title":"Samba installation","meta_description":"\bSamba is the standard windows interoperability suite of programs for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file and print services.","og_description":null,"og_image":null,"og_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"authors":[{"name":"Daegyun Na","slug":"daegyun","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/author/daegyun/","bio":"\"The greatest discovery of my generation is that a human being can alter his life by altering his attitudes\"","cover_image":null,"profile_image":"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/author-dg-photo.png","twitter":"@nadaegyun","facebook":"nadaegyun","website":"https://www.nadaegyun.com","coverImageSharp":null,"profileImageSharp":null}],"primary_author":{"name":"Daegyun Na","slug":"daegyun","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/author/daegyun/","bio":"\"The greatest discovery of my generation is that a human being can alter his life by altering his attitudes\"","cover_image":null,"profile_image":"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/author-dg-photo.png","twitter":"@nadaegyun","facebook":"nadaegyun","website":"https://www.nadaegyun.com","coverImageSharp":null,"profileImageSharp":{"base":"author-dg-photo.png","publicURL":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/author-dg-photo.png","imageMeta":{"width":100,"height":100},"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/0d540/author-dg-photo.png","srcSet":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/8c64d/author-dg-photo.png 28w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/ad6c8/author-dg-photo.png 55w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/0d540/author-dg-photo.png 100w","srcWebp":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/bef64/author-dg-photo.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/0349d/author-dg-photo.webp 28w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/1091e/author-dg-photo.webp 55w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/bef64/author-dg-photo.webp 100w","sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px"}}}},"primary_tag":{"name":"RaspberryPi","slug":"raspberrypi","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/tag/raspberrypi/","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public","featureImageSharp":null},"tags":[{"name":"RaspberryPi","slug":"raspberrypi","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/tag/raspberrypi/","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public","featureImageSharp":null}],"plaintext":"> File sharing and print services between Windows and Linux even Mac osX are\npossible with Samba.\n\bSamba [https://www.samba.org] is the standard windows interoperability suite of\nprograms for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file\nand print services for all clients using the SMB/CIFS protocol, such as all\nversions of DOS and Windows, OS/2, Linux and many others.\n\nHow to install Samba\nBefore you install Samba it is recommanded to update Raspberry OS software\npackage update. Please input followings in terminal.\n\nsudo apt-get update\n\nsudo apt-get upgrade\n\nthen install samba inputting following command in terminal.\n\nsudo apt-get install samba samba-common-bin\n\nIt is recommanded to use WINS settings from DHCP if you get IP from DHCP server\nfrom your router.\n\nID and Pasword setting for Samba\nIt is required to set up ID and password for Samba and here pi as samba ID will\nbe used.\n\nsudo smbpasswd -a pi\n\nType new password.\n\nRetype new password.\n\nIf you want to use your favorite ID you should type it at the end.\n\nsudo smbpasswd -a your-favorite-ID\n\nex)\nsudo smbpasswd -a abcd\n\nand then restart samba or reboot Raspberry Pi.\n\nsudo systemctl restart smbd\n\nYou will find RASPBERRYPI in your network from the PC you want to connect to\nRaspberry Pi.\n\nClick Raspberry Pi in your network then it will be connected\n\nType Samba ID and password.\n\nNow you can connect to your Raspberry Pi in your network.\n\nHow to assign full permission on your Raspberry Pi\nIf you want to have full permission with Samba ID on your raspberry Pi, you need\nto add following information in the end of smb.conf.\n\nFirst, edit smb.conf using vi editor as follows.\n\nsudo vi /etc/samba/smb.conf\n\nThen input following information on the end of smb.conf\n\n[pi]\n   comment = pi shared folder\n   path = /home/pi\n   valid users = pi\n   browseable = yes\n   guest ok = no\n   read only = no\n   create mask = 0777\n\nIf you don't know how to use vi editor, please refer to this post.","html":"<blockquote>File sharing and print services between Windows and Linux even Mac osX are possible with Samba.</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/img.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>\b<a href=\"https://www.samba.org\">Samba</a> is the standard windows interoperability suite of programs for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file and print services for all clients using the SMB/CIFS protocol, such as all versions of DOS and Windows, OS/2, Linux and many others.</p><h2 id=\"how-to-install-samba\">How to install Samba</h2><p>Before you install Samba it is recommanded to update Raspberry OS software package update. Please input followings in terminal.</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo apt-get update</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052801.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052802.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo apt-get upgrade</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-3.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052803.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052804.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>then install samba inputting following command in terminal.</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo apt-get install samba samba-common-bin</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-5.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052805.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>It is recommanded to use WINS settings from DHCP if you get IP from DHCP server from your router.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052806.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052807.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><h2 id=\"id-and-pasword-setting-for-samba\">ID and Pasword setting for Samba</h2><p>It is required to set up ID and password for Samba and here pi as samba ID will be used.</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo smbpasswd -a pi</code></pre><p>Type new password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052809.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>Retype new password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052810.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052811.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>If you want to use your favorite ID you should type it at the end.</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo smbpasswd -a your-favorite-ID\n\nex)\nsudo smbpasswd -a abcd</code></pre><p>and then restart samba or reboot Raspberry Pi.</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo systemctl restart smbd</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052812.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>You will find RASPBERRYPI in your network from the PC you want to connect to Raspberry Pi.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052813.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>Click Raspberry Pi in your network then it will be connected</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052814.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>Type Samba ID and password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052815.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>Now you can connect to your Raspberry Pi in your network.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052816.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><h2 id=\"how-to-assign-full-permission-on-your-raspberry-pi\">How to assign full permission on your Raspberry Pi</h2><p>If you want to have full permission with Samba ID on your raspberry Pi, you need to add following information in the end of smb.conf.</p><p>First, edit smb.conf using vi editor as follows.</p><pre><code>sudo vi /etc/samba/smb.conf</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052817.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>Then input following information on the end of smb.conf</p><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">[pi]\n   comment = pi shared folder\n   path = /home/pi\n   valid users = pi\n   browseable = yes\n   guest ok = no\n   read only = no\n   create mask = 0777</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-3.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052818.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052819.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>If you don't know how to use vi editor, please refer to this post.</p>","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/raspberry-pi-how-to-install-samba/","canonical_url":"https://www.nadaegyun.com/raspberry-pi-how-to-install-samba","uuid":"fb2f94c0-f9c7-4b14-a849-0b318b52edd6","codeinjection_foot":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_styles":null,"comment_id":"60b08e9903ca89001c10894c","reading_time":3,"childHtmlRehype":{"html":"<blockquote>File sharing and print services between Windows and Linux even Mac osX are possible with Samba.</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/img.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>\b<a href=\"https://www.samba.org\">Samba</a> is the standard windows interoperability suite of programs for Linux and Unix. It is free software, secure, stable and fast file and print services for all clients using the SMB/CIFS protocol, such as all versions of DOS and Windows, OS/2, Linux and many others.</p><h2 id=\"how-to-install-samba\">How to install Samba</h2><p>Before you install Samba it is recommanded to update Raspberry OS software package update. Please input followings in terminal.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> update</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052801.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052802.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> upgrade</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-3.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052803.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052804.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>then install samba inputting following command in terminal.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> samba samba-common-bin</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-5.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052805.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>It is recommanded to use WINS settings from DHCP if you get IP from DHCP server from your router.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052806.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052807.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><h2 id=\"id-and-pasword-setting-for-samba\">ID and Pasword setting for Samba</h2><p>It is required to set up ID and password for Samba and here pi as samba ID will be used.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> smbpasswd -a pi</code></pre></div><p>Type new password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052809.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Retype new password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052810.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052811.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>If you want to use your favorite ID you should type it at the end.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> smbpasswd -a your-favorite-ID\n\nex<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> smbpasswd -a abcd</code></pre></div><p>and then restart samba or reboot Raspberry Pi.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> systemctl restart smbd</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052812.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>You will find RASPBERRYPI in your network from the PC you want to connect to Raspberry Pi.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052813.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Click Raspberry Pi in your network then it will be connected</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052814.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Type Samba ID and password.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-4.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052815.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Now you can connect to your Raspberry Pi in your network.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052816.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><h2 id=\"how-to-assign-full-permission-on-your-raspberry-pi\">How to assign full permission on your Raspberry Pi</h2><p>If you want to have full permission with Samba ID on your raspberry Pi, you need to add following information in the end of smb.conf.</p><p>First, edit smb.conf using vi editor as follows.</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo vi /etc/samba/smb.conf</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-1.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052817.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Then input following information on the end of smb.conf</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>pi<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n   comment <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pi shared folder\n   path <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> /home/pi\n   valid <span class=\"token function\">users</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pi\n   browseable <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">yes</span>\n   guest ok <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> no\n   <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">read</span> only <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> no\n   create mask <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> 0777</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-3.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/2021052818.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blo